# Example .npmrc — DO NOT COMMIT YOUR REAL .npmrc
# Copy this file to .npmrc and fill in your own token.
#
# Get a token at: https://www.npmjs.com/settings/~/tokens
# Recommended: "Granular Access Token" with "Bypass 2FA" for local dev,
# OR enable 2FA on your npm account and use a regular publish token.
#
# Alternatively, log in interactively:
#   npm login
# (This writes to ~/.npmrc, which is also fine and not committed.)

# registry.npmjs.org/:_authToken=npm_YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
